CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 16, 1966, pg. 1B reads:"Young Set Have Fun Too At Alpha Dance - Between Sets - The Student Union of the University of Pittsburgh was the scene of youthful gaiety when Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity sponsored a benefit dance for the United Negro College Fund. It was under the supervision of the UNCF's Women's Division, headed by Miss Nancy Lee..."
TitMainTitle: Women and men standing along edge of ballroom in University of Pittsburgh Student Union for Alpha Phi Alpha benefit dance for United Negro College Fund
